<item>
            <title>[LU-733] Test Framework applies a timestamp when gathering logs after an error and this should be removed.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-733</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;gather_logs appeneds a timestamp as part of the filename, this serves no purpose because the name is unique to the test causing the error and the logs will only be gather once.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In fact more than serving no purpose the timestamp actually makes the filename used &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;intentionaly&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; is impossible to predict.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This time stamp should be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
